1
00:00:53,208 --> 00:00:55,125
That was a great meal.

2
00:00:55,208 --> 00:00:56,541
Why don't you come
with me to see

3
00:00:56,625 --> 00:00:57,916
the Imperial Operetta Troupe?

4
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:58,916
Oh!

5
00:01:03,625 --> 00:01:06,291
I wonder if grandpa
will come visit us?

6
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:26,125
Oh yes.

7
00:01:26,208 --> 00:01:28,166
I couldn't agree with you more.

8
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:30,083
Mommy let's bring home a cake!

9
00:01:30,166 --> 00:01:30,708
Yeah!

10
00:01:30,791 --> 00:01:32,750
That sounds yummy!

11
00:02:09,541 --> 00:02:12,500
Let's raise the curtains now.

12
00:05:15,125 --> 00:05:17,375
Thank you very much for
attending this performance

13
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:20,583
held in our Great
Imperial Theater House.

14
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:23,000
We would like to express
our deep appreciation

15
00:05:23,083 --> 00:05:24,791
for your patronage.

16
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:31,208
Great work, everyone!

17
00:05:31,291 --> 00:05:32,458
We all did great work.

18
00:05:32,541 --> 00:05:33,333
--Good job!
--Great work!

19
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:33,833
Thanks for your announcement.

20
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:34,916
Sure.

21
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,875
Wasn't that an
amazing audience, Leni?!

22
00:05:36,958 --> 00:05:38,208
I couldn't believe it!

23
00:05:38,291 --> 00:05:40,583
I know-the crowd was
especially wonderful today.

24
00:05:40,666 --> 00:05:43,166
We should be grateful for
an audience such as that.

25
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:45,041
Yeah, you've got
that right Ms. Maria!

26
00:05:45,125 --> 00:05:47,875
It was almost as if we were
one with the audience today!

27
00:05:47,958 --> 00:05:49,875
It was so much fun wasn't it.

28
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:54,125
Well, it seems you all
did do a nice job today.

29
00:05:54,208 --> 00:05:55,666
Are you feeling all right?!

30
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:58,375
It's a rare occasion for Ms.
Sumire to give us a compliment!

31
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:00,416
That's for sure!
Wow. What an honor.

32
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,333
I've got to admit it
feels good even though

33
00:06:02,416 --> 00:06:03,875
I'm exhausted
from all the hard work.

34
00:06:03,958 --> 00:06:06,958
Well you deserve it-You've
worked hard all year Orihime.

35
00:06:07,041 --> 00:06:09,291
That's true you have - but
I think that Ms. Kanna

36
00:06:09,375 --> 00:06:11,250
has worked the hardest
out of all of us!

37
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:12,833
Oh really?!

38
00:06:12,916 --> 00:06:15,375
Well I don't recall Ms. Kanna
exerting herself particularly.

39
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:16,583
What?

40
00:06:16,666 --> 00:06:17,291
You're the only one
who disagrees ya know.

41
00:06:17,375 --> 00:06:18,958
This is our theatre.

42
00:06:19,041 --> 00:06:22,208
This is where we, the members of
the Imperial Operetta Troupe;

43
00:06:22,291 --> 00:06:25,500
"The Flower Division," come
together to give our sweat,

44
00:06:25,583 --> 00:06:29,875
tears, and hopes all combined
into one, to shine brightly.

45
00:06:29,958 --> 00:06:33,958
There's no place I'd rather be
than right here, right now.

46
00:06:34,041 --> 00:06:35,833
That's what makes me happy.

47
00:06:36,916 --> 00:06:37,666
Surprise!

48
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:39,041
Happy birthday to you, Leni!

49
00:06:39,125 --> 00:06:40,708
Happy birthday Leni!

50
00:06:40,791 --> 00:06:43,666
Congratulations -
you're 17 now, Leni.

51
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:44,875
That's true - Thank you.

52
00:06:44,958 --> 00:06:47,750
Wait for me you guys -
I'll be right there!

53
00:06:47,833 --> 00:06:49,083
Oh dear...

54
00:06:49,166 --> 00:06:50,333
Don't leave me out!

55
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:52,458
Please! I'm coming right now!

56
00:06:59,291 --> 00:07:02,541
Sorry about that -
Happy birthday Leni...

57
00:07:02,625 --> 00:07:05,166
That's all right -
Thanks' Sakura.

58
00:07:05,250 --> 00:07:08,416
I'll never understand how
you manage to be such a klutz.

59
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:11,708
I suppose you'll always have
the co-ordination of a Bafoon.

60
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,458
Ah, isn't the
Flower Division wonderful.

61
00:07:17,541 --> 00:07:18,375
Hi there ladies.

62
00:07:18,458 --> 00:07:19,458
Good work.

63
00:07:19,541 --> 00:07:21,375
Merry Christmas
and Happy birthday Leni!

64
00:07:21,458 --> 00:07:23,208
Captain Kayama.

65
00:07:23,291 --> 00:07:24,625
I was just thinking...

66
00:07:24,708 --> 00:07:27,125
...With the Flower Division
Captain Ichiro Oogami

67
00:07:27,208 --> 00:07:28,666
being away in Paris and all,

68
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:30,958
I thought that I'd try
to cheer everyone up.

69
00:07:31,041 --> 00:07:34,708
But Mr. Kayama-right now Maria
is our temporary captain!

70
00:07:34,791 --> 00:07:36,500
Boy, it seems to me
like we were having

71
00:07:36,583 --> 00:07:38,875
a whole lot more fun before
Mr. Kayama showed up.

72
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:40,958
Hey! C'mon now!
We can still have fun.

73
00:07:41,041 --> 00:07:42,916
Let's live it up tonight!-Okay?

74
00:08:01,333 --> 00:08:02,458
This doesn't look
as interesting.

75
00:08:02,541 --> 00:08:04,333
That one looks better,
don't you think?

76
00:08:04,416 --> 00:08:05,125
Oh, ' Sumire?

77
00:08:05,208 --> 00:08:07,166
Is that you?

78
00:08:07,250 --> 00:08:08,750
Oh, Ms. Maria!

79
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:10,625
Well, what a coincidence.

80
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:13,250
I'm surprised to see you
here ' Sumire -

81
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:15,708
I didn't know
you liked these films.

82
00:08:15,791 --> 00:08:18,458
Well I just thought that
I should try and understand

83
00:08:18,541 --> 00:08:22,208
more about the films
the common people see.

84
00:08:22,291 --> 00:08:24,416
Would you care
to join me, Ms. Maria?

85
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:25,583
Eh?

86
00:08:29,708 --> 00:08:32,916
A powerful friend has arrived
at the imperial capital Tokyo;

87
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:34,958
the United States of America.

88
00:08:35,041 --> 00:08:37,291
Among the many corporations
to be found there,

89
00:08:37,375 --> 00:08:39,625
the Douglas-Stewart
Corporation stands out

90
00:08:39,708 --> 00:08:41,458
with its advanced science.

91
00:08:41,541 --> 00:08:44,416
Mr. Brent Furlong, the young
president of Douglas-Stewart,

92
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,750
is a man passionate
about charity work.

93
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:49,250
Amazed at the rapid pace
of our nation's recovery

94
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:51,375
and the strong work
ethic of her people...

95
00:08:51,458 --> 00:08:53,875
Excuse me, Ms. Maria?

96
00:08:55,375 --> 00:08:56,916
Is something bothering you?

97
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:57,875
I'm sorry.

98
00:08:57,958 --> 00:08:59,166
It's nothing, really.

99
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:00,833
Oh-all right then.

100
00:09:46,791 --> 00:09:48,416
Uh, Thank you
for coming, Ma'am!

101
00:10:05,375 --> 00:10:06,833
Excuse me.

102
00:10:06,916 --> 00:10:08,625
Do either of you speak English?

103
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:11,500
Uh, sorry I'm not
very good with English.

104
00:10:11,583 --> 00:10:12,416
Ms. Sakura!

105
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:13,666
What?

106
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:16,833
Oh, I'm not very good
with English either...

107
00:10:16,916 --> 00:10:18,708
How are-you?

108
00:10:18,791 --> 00:10:19,875
Did I get it wrong?

109
00:10:19,958 --> 00:10:21,041
Let's see...

110
00:10:21,125 --> 00:10:22,291
Nice-to-meet you!

111
00:10:22,375 --> 00:10:23,541
Hmm?

112
00:10:23,625 --> 00:10:25,208
What are you trying to say?

113
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:28,291
You are not making
any sense ' at all.

114
00:10:28,375 --> 00:10:30,375
Will you please
stop wasting my time!

115
00:10:30,458 --> 00:10:32,375
Uh, My name is Sakura!

116
00:10:32,458 --> 00:10:35,208
Sakura is a cherry!

117
00:10:35,291 --> 00:10:36,375
Um cherry...

118
00:10:36,458 --> 00:10:38,333
Ms. Sakura, you're
not making any sense.

119
00:10:38,416 --> 00:10:40,708
Please calm down...!

120
00:10:40,791 --> 00:10:41,625
I'm sorry.

121
00:10:41,708 --> 00:10:42,583
I was just playing.

122
00:10:42,666 --> 00:10:43,666
Huh?

123
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:46,583
Where can I find
the owner Mr. Yoneda?

124
00:10:46,666 --> 00:10:47,875
Mr. Yoneda...?

125
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:49,666
The manager...?

126
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:53,125
I see, so the Elders Institute
has finally decided to setup

127
00:10:53,208 --> 00:10:55,375
a Fighting Troupe
even in America.

128
00:10:55,458 --> 00:10:56,666
Yes-Sir.

129
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:58,375
Following in the footsteps
of Tokyo and Paris,

130
00:10:58,458 --> 00:11:00,125
the Third City
Defense Program will be

131
00:11:00,208 --> 00:11:01,250
the New York Fighting Troupe.

132
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:02,833
Really?

133
00:11:02,916 --> 00:11:05,541
So, why did you decide to come
all the way out here to Tokyo?

134
00:11:05,625 --> 00:11:08,041
Tokyo has defended itself
against two Invasions

135
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:11,458
by the demons ' and Paris
has just repelled the Parisy.

136
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:14,125
To learn from these successes,
it would seem more efficient

137
00:11:14,208 --> 00:11:16,375
if I actually worked in the
field with them rather then

138
00:11:16,458 --> 00:11:17,625
study them from afar.

139
00:11:17,708 --> 00:11:18,958
Efficient...

140
00:11:19,041 --> 00:11:20,416
eh?

141
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:22,250
As of today,
I have been assigned

142
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:24,708
to the Imperial Fighting
Troupe, Flower Division.

143
00:11:24,791 --> 00:11:27,666
Lachette Altair
reporting for duty, Sir.

144
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:29,541
I look forward
to serving under you.

145
00:11:29,625 --> 00:11:31,791
So I suppose you
already got permission

146
00:11:31,875 --> 00:11:35,166
from the Elders Institute
to do this, eh?

147
00:11:35,250 --> 00:11:37,375
And if I'm not mistaken, ah...

148
00:11:37,458 --> 00:11:41,250
...You probably brought your own
Eisenkleid to Japan, didn't you?

149
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:42,375
Where is it?

150
00:11:42,458 --> 00:11:44,208
We'll have to go
pick it up right away.

151
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:45,875
That's not a problem, Sir.

152
00:11:45,958 --> 00:11:48,000
I brought it with me
on the truck.

153
00:11:50,625 --> 00:11:51,708
I should have known.

154
00:11:51,791 --> 00:11:54,041
As always you've got
it all worked out.

155
00:11:54,125 --> 00:11:57,333
I merely chose the most
efficient course of action, Sir.

156
00:12:05,791 --> 00:12:06,583
Well, well.

157
00:12:06,666 --> 00:12:09,208
What to do now...

158
00:12:09,291 --> 00:12:10,791
She was against the break up.

159
00:12:10,875 --> 00:12:13,125
She wanted the Star Division
to stay together.

160
00:12:13,208 --> 00:12:15,458
She more than anyone else
took pride in her role

161
00:12:15,541 --> 00:12:18,833
as a guardian of the people
against the darkness.

162
00:12:18,916 --> 00:12:20,166
I understand.

163
00:12:20,250 --> 00:12:22,458
But however exceptional
their skills and abilities

164
00:12:22,541 --> 00:12:25,500
were as a unit they
were still too fragile.

165
00:12:25,583 --> 00:12:27,125
We'll see if Lachette
has come to realize

166
00:12:27,208 --> 00:12:30,875
the reason why the Star
Division was broken up or not.

167
00:12:31,791 --> 00:12:34,000
Our imperial capital,
Tokyo, is enjoying

168
00:12:34,083 --> 00:12:35,791
great prosperity at the moment.

169
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:37,416
What are you
worried about then?

170
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,958
Have we not rushed to improve
the city's infrastructure

171
00:12:40,041 --> 00:12:41,791
at the expense of her defenses.

172
00:12:41,875 --> 00:12:44,708
You're needlessly raising
a cause for alarm.

173
00:12:44,791 --> 00:12:47,541
What exactly do you think
we've come here to address?

174
00:12:47,625 --> 00:12:50,208
Our imperial capital
is open in four directions,

175
00:12:50,291 --> 00:12:52,875
connecting us to
other areas via waterways.

176
00:12:52,958 --> 00:12:55,375
This geographic advantage
has brought the prosperity

177
00:12:55,458 --> 00:12:57,875
we enjoy today, but we
may have also brought in

178
00:12:57,958 --> 00:12:59,750
diseased elements
in the process.

179
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:01,541
Are you talking about America?

180
00:13:01,625 --> 00:13:04,625
Even if that was the case,
the capital can certainly rely

181
00:13:04,708 --> 00:13:07,250
on the Imperial Fighting
Troupe for its defense.

182
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:09,166
Do you think it's wise
to be completely dependent

183
00:13:09,250 --> 00:13:10,583
on those young girls?

184
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:12,916
No doubt there are issues
that must be addressed,

185
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,416
but these are rather trivial.

186
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:17,208
We needn't look further than
our capital and Paris to see

187
00:13:17,291 --> 00:13:20,083
that the Fighting Troupe
program is a success.

188
00:13:20,166 --> 00:13:22,791
Our nation needs a capital
city, and a city needs

189
00:13:22,875 --> 00:13:25,000
to be open to the free
movement of the people

190
00:13:25,083 --> 00:13:27,250
for it to be
prosperous and thrive.

191
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:30,041
It is unavoidable for the
bright lights of prosperity

192
00:13:30,125 --> 00:13:32,916
to create and give rise
to the shadows of darkness.

193
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:36,333
We must be prepared to accept
this and learn to live with it.

194
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:38,875
And I trust ' that
all of you understand.

195
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:41,416
What might be the opinion of
the government on this issue,

196
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,250
Mr. Tanuma?

197
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:45,000
Well it appears...

198
00:13:45,083 --> 00:13:46,583
...That for this city
to develop further

199
00:13:46,666 --> 00:13:49,208
as an occult stronghold,
clearly our existing spiritual

200
00:13:49,291 --> 00:13:52,416
quarantine measures will likely
offer inadequate protection.

201
00:13:52,500 --> 00:13:55,000
Therefore, there really is
nothing else we know of

202
00:13:55,083 --> 00:13:58,000
that can replace the Fighting
Troupe Flower Division

203
00:13:58,083 --> 00:14:00,000
at this time.

204
00:14:00,083 --> 00:14:03,208
However in the spirit of
being constantly mindful

205
00:14:03,291 --> 00:14:05,916
of our surroundings, I believe
we should not shy away

206
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,750
from infusing new blood
to meet different challenges

207
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:10,416
as the need arises.

208
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:13,666
Yes, I dare say darkness
will come upon us again.

209
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:16,166
But if this city should
fall, that would mean

210
00:14:16,250 --> 00:14:19,375
the entire nation would succumb
to the onslaught of darkness.

211
00:14:19,458 --> 00:14:21,500
That must never happen!

212
00:14:22,375 --> 00:14:24,833
A real cute face
from America, huh?

213
00:14:26,291 --> 00:14:27,541
There you are Ms. Sakura.

214
00:14:27,625 --> 00:14:29,041
Oh, thank you very much.

215
00:14:29,125 --> 00:14:32,166
So tell us Ms. Sakura
is this new girl from America

216
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:34,000
really as beautiful
as they say?

217
00:14:34,083 --> 00:14:36,958
Actually she's speaking
with Mr. Yoneda right now.

218
00:14:37,041 --> 00:14:39,208
When she comes by
you can see for yourself.

219
00:14:39,291 --> 00:14:41,375
But I'm interested in hearing
what you thought about her

220
00:14:41,458 --> 00:14:42,875
- What was your
first impression?

221
00:14:42,958 --> 00:14:45,250
Why do you wanna know that?

222
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:47,125
It usually takes more
than one pair of eyes

223
00:14:47,208 --> 00:14:49,291
to get a true
understanding of something.

224
00:14:49,375 --> 00:14:51,583
Now I don't know how
much of a beauty she is

225
00:14:51,666 --> 00:14:53,416
but we've all gotta see her
with our own eyes

226
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:54,833
to get to the
"heart of the matter."

227
00:14:54,916 --> 00:14:56,708
Oh really - Is that so?

228
00:14:57,708 --> 00:14:58,791
Ah!

229
00:14:58,875 --> 00:15:00,916
Here comes that
"heart of the matter" now!

230
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:03,916
How embarrassing.

231
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,916
She must've heard
every word we said.

232
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:08,833
Well you know they say that
"curiosity killed the cat."

233
00:15:08,916 --> 00:15:09,791
Where'd you hear that?

234
00:15:09,875 --> 00:15:11,458
It's just a Western saying.

235
00:15:11,541 --> 00:15:14,291
Oh I see so now you're trying
to act like an America.

236
00:15:14,375 --> 00:15:16,041
No I'm not!

237
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:17,791
Ms. Sakura!

238
00:15:31,958 --> 00:15:33,125
Wow, you weren't kidding!

239
00:15:33,208 --> 00:15:34,541
She's a real beauty all right!

240
00:15:34,625 --> 00:15:35,916
Told you.

241
00:16:23,041 --> 00:16:25,666
I know what you mean, Sir.

242
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:32,500
This country is
in need of a true king.

243
00:16:32,583 --> 00:16:36,833
Rationalism demands that the
world be united under one will.

244
00:16:36,916 --> 00:16:38,875
We must teach them that.

245
00:16:38,958 --> 00:16:41,916
I knew you were going
to say that, Sir.

246
00:16:49,791 --> 00:16:51,166
Beautiful.

247
00:17:37,583 --> 00:17:40,458
Descending Demons have
appeared in Zaimoku-Chou.

248
00:17:40,541 --> 00:17:43,083
The number confirmed
so far is 13.

249
00:17:43,166 --> 00:17:45,000
A fire has broken out,
but the Moon Division

250
00:17:45,083 --> 00:17:47,541
is currently at work
putting it out.

251
00:17:47,625 --> 00:17:49,750
Fire can spread quickly
this season, so be mindful

252
00:17:49,833 --> 00:17:52,083
of the surrounding
houses during combat.

253
00:17:52,166 --> 00:17:52,958
Yes, Sir!

254
00:17:53,041 --> 00:17:54,375
Right.

255
00:17:54,458 --> 00:17:56,500
Imperial Fighting Troupe,
Flower Division move out!

256
00:17:56,583 --> 00:17:57,708
Yes-Sir!

