274
00:20:48,458 --> 00:20:49,666
Descent complete.

275
00:21:15,958 --> 00:21:18,166
Moving Gourai -
Go into launch position.

276
00:22:10,166 --> 00:22:12,208
Just cleared Asakusa Station!

277
00:23:13,125 --> 00:23:14,541
Don't let your guard down!

278
00:23:14,625 --> 00:23:15,750
Yes, Ma'am!

279
00:23:57,625 --> 00:23:58,458
Ah!!

280
00:23:58,541 --> 00:23:59,583
Leni!

281
00:24:21,541 --> 00:24:22,750
Lachette!!

282
00:24:35,958 --> 00:24:37,750
Stop fighting on your own!

283
00:24:37,833 --> 00:24:39,625
Don't forget
we fight as a team!

284
00:24:39,708 --> 00:24:40,750
Understood?!

285
00:25:03,583 --> 00:25:04,333
What is that?

286
00:25:04,416 --> 00:25:05,208
Is it a friend or an enemy?

287
00:25:05,291 --> 00:25:06,166
What could that have been?

288
00:25:06,250 --> 00:25:07,041
What the hell's going on?

289
00:25:07,125 --> 00:25:08,458
What is that?

290
00:25:32,791 --> 00:25:35,000
I dare say,
what could they be?

291
00:25:35,083 --> 00:25:37,958
Heh, How the hell
are we supposed to find out?

292
00:25:41,916 --> 00:25:44,208
We were all
quite surprised, Sir.

293
00:25:44,291 --> 00:25:47,166
A humanoid steam unit
of unknown origin?

294
00:25:47,250 --> 00:25:48,083
Yes, Sir.

295
00:25:48,166 --> 00:25:49,250
Hm...

296
00:25:49,333 --> 00:25:51,708
Well, I suppose
that it has all started...

297
00:25:51,791 --> 00:25:53,625
What do you mean, Sir.

298
00:25:53,708 --> 00:25:56,166
Well ' you know that
in a capitalist nation

299
00:25:56,250 --> 00:25:59,250
freedom means the
freedom to compete.

300
00:25:59,333 --> 00:26:00,416
Huh?

301
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:02,958
I just hope this won't get
too complicated.

302
00:26:03,041 --> 00:26:06,666
Uh Sir I'd like to talk to you
about the new company member.

303
00:26:06,750 --> 00:26:07,625
Huh?

304
00:26:07,708 --> 00:26:09,708
Lachette?
And what about her?

305
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:18,208
Sounds like this is
going to get complicated.

306
00:26:23,875 --> 00:26:25,375
Who the hell is this?!

307
00:26:25,458 --> 00:26:26,916
Lachette Altair...

308
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:28,625
She used to be our
captain ' when we were

309
00:26:28,708 --> 00:26:29,958
in the Star Division.

310
00:26:30,041 --> 00:26:30,666
What?

311
00:26:30,750 --> 00:26:32,041
You know this person?

312
00:26:32,125 --> 00:26:34,041
I see, then what is
she doing here?

313
00:26:34,125 --> 00:26:36,000
I have no idea.

314
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:40,125
Lachette!

315
00:26:40,208 --> 00:26:41,375
Hi, Orihime.

316
00:26:41,458 --> 00:26:44,000
It's been a long time!

317
00:26:44,083 --> 00:26:46,041
You two have already met?

318
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:50,125
Lachette, it's been so long!

319
00:26:50,208 --> 00:26:52,125
It certainly has, Orihime.

320
00:26:52,208 --> 00:26:53,916
You're looking well.

321
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:55,291
Oh!-And...

322
00:26:55,375 --> 00:26:57,083
You too, Leni...

323
00:26:57,166 --> 00:26:58,958
What are you doing here?

324
00:26:59,958 --> 00:27:13,666
Leni!

325
00:27:13,750 --> 00:27:15,750
Wait for me Leni!

326
00:27:17,166 --> 00:27:18,583
Hmm...

327
00:27:18,666 --> 00:27:21,416
Well it looks like Leni is
still uncomfortable around you.

328
00:27:21,500 --> 00:27:23,916
Since we'll all be members
of Flower Division

329
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:25,083
this will be a problem...

330
00:27:25,166 --> 00:27:27,250
Is that so?!

331
00:27:27,333 --> 00:27:29,000
I am Lachette Altair.

332
00:27:29,083 --> 00:27:31,750
I hope that we will
all work well together.

333
00:27:34,583 --> 00:27:38,416
And so it has been decided
that this unit will be leased

334
00:27:38,500 --> 00:27:42,666
to the Army along with technical
advisors from Douglas-Stewart.

335
00:27:44,083 --> 00:27:46,458
While we are still
in the trial stages...

336
00:27:46,541 --> 00:27:48,375
...I'm certain they'll
be adopted into service

337
00:27:48,458 --> 00:27:49,708
within a year.

338
00:27:49,791 --> 00:27:51,041
Once that happens...

339
00:27:51,125 --> 00:27:53,625
... There will be no need
for the Flower Division

340
00:27:53,708 --> 00:27:55,916
And, we will no longer have
to expose young girls

341
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:57,750
to unnecessary dangers.

342
00:27:57,833 --> 00:27:59,833
Will we, Count Hanakouji?

343
00:27:59,916 --> 00:28:01,916
Mr. Tanuma, if you
have something to say

344
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:04,333
I'd appreciate it if
you'd say it directly!

345
00:28:05,458 --> 00:28:07,500
My apologies, Sir.

346
00:28:07,583 --> 00:28:10,041
I was simply trying to point
out the winds of change

347
00:28:10,125 --> 00:28:12,958
to my senior
officer - that's all.

348
00:28:13,041 --> 00:28:16,583
What is new to us now will
eventually become obsolete.

349
00:28:16,666 --> 00:28:19,416
While this latest demonstration
was typically American

350
00:28:19,500 --> 00:28:20,875
in its recklessness...

351
00:28:20,958 --> 00:28:23,291
I believe now you know just
how capable the unmanned,

352
00:28:23,375 --> 00:28:26,833
low-cost humanoid steam
unit "Yafqiel" is.

353
00:28:26,916 --> 00:28:28,208
What grandstanding!

354
00:28:28,291 --> 00:28:30,875
You knew of this beforehand
didn't you Tanuma?!

355
00:28:30,958 --> 00:28:32,791
But of course, Sir!

356
00:28:32,875 --> 00:28:36,541
Only a fool would show his hand
before all the cards were dealt.

357
00:28:36,625 --> 00:28:39,875
Are you implying that you treat
governance the same as gambling?

358
00:28:39,958 --> 00:28:42,458
No my dear Count,
the analogy is often made

359
00:28:42,541 --> 00:28:44,625
that life is one big gamble.

360
00:28:44,708 --> 00:28:46,583
Is it not more important
that the government take

361
00:28:46,666 --> 00:28:50,541
proper action than worry about
how it words these actions?

362
00:29:22,625 --> 00:29:25,791
My how Leni
has certainly changed...

363
00:31:08,458 --> 00:31:10,083
A defect.

364
00:31:10,166 --> 00:31:12,208
Please, wait a minute.

365
00:31:12,291 --> 00:31:13,541
This will never do!

366
00:31:13,625 --> 00:31:15,416
If they find out...

367
00:31:17,791 --> 00:31:20,375
Please refrain from
such imprudent statements.

368
00:31:20,458 --> 00:31:22,375
Or else our amicable
relationship will

369
00:31:22,458 --> 00:31:25,208
have to be terminated
right here.

370
00:31:25,291 --> 00:31:27,833
Is that what you want Tanuma?

371
00:31:29,250 --> 00:31:34,083
You and I are not equal
partners in this endeavor.

372
00:31:34,166 --> 00:31:37,083
You'd do well
to remember that.

373
00:32:03,708 --> 00:32:04,500
Make way!

374
00:32:04,583 --> 00:32:05,208
Watch out!

375
00:32:05,291 --> 00:32:07,041
Comin' through!!

376
00:32:07,125 --> 00:32:08,750
Move it!-Step aside!

377
00:32:10,250 --> 00:32:11,625
That's wonderful Ms. Kanna!

378
00:32:11,708 --> 00:32:12,916
Faster please-Faster!

379
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:14,625
No problem-leave it to me!

380
00:32:14,708 --> 00:32:15,916
Hii-ya!!

381
00:32:26,583 --> 00:32:28,791
Kasumi is it all right
if we look inside

382
00:32:28,875 --> 00:32:30,500
some of the stores here?

383
00:32:30,583 --> 00:32:33,625
Not yet Iris, but we can after
we go and pray in the shrine.

384
00:32:33,708 --> 00:32:35,791
Aww. That's boring!

385
00:32:42,416 --> 00:32:44,125
The texture
of this is reminiscent

386
00:32:44,208 --> 00:32:45,875
of the Italian dish, gnocchi.

387
00:32:45,958 --> 00:32:46,750
Gnocchi?

388
00:32:46,833 --> 00:32:48,500
Well that's a funny name.

389
00:32:48,583 --> 00:32:49,541
Really?

390
00:32:49,625 --> 00:32:51,250
I think the Japanese
names for foods

391
00:32:51,333 --> 00:32:53,750
are even stranger
sounding than that.

392
00:32:53,833 --> 00:33:00,250
Yuba ganmodoki tokoroten
kiritannpo kinchaku...

393
00:33:00,333 --> 00:33:01,666
Hmph

394
00:33:01,750 --> 00:33:03,708
And these are miso
rice cake balls,

395
00:33:03,791 --> 00:33:06,250
but where is all
the miso sauce?!

396
00:33:06,333 --> 00:33:08,916
It's mitarashi, not miso!

397
00:33:11,666 --> 00:33:15,083
And how on Earth is someone
supposed to eat the last one?!!

398
00:33:15,166 --> 00:33:16,541
Aah...

399
00:33:16,625 --> 00:33:18,416
Aah...

400
00:33:22,458 --> 00:33:23,625
Thank you!

401
00:33:23,708 --> 00:33:25,958
And now our master juggler
will add two more!

402
00:33:28,125 --> 00:33:29,208
And another one!

403
00:33:29,291 --> 00:33:31,333
Oh!

404
00:33:38,291 --> 00:33:40,166
Hey! What the hell is this?!

405
00:33:40,250 --> 00:33:42,875
Your wishes will not be
granted-Your health may suffer.

406
00:33:42,958 --> 00:33:44,416
Lost possessions
will not return...

407
00:33:44,500 --> 00:33:46,208
Romance and
relationships will sour!

408
00:33:46,291 --> 00:33:47,750
What's the big idea here?!

409
00:33:47,833 --> 00:33:50,916
What have I done in my
short life to deserve this?!!

410
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,750
Don't let it bother you, Kouran.

411
00:33:52,833 --> 00:33:54,875
If your fortune
is really all that bad -

412
00:33:54,958 --> 00:33:56,708
then that means that
it can't get any worse.

413
00:33:56,791 --> 00:33:59,541
What about yours?
- Let's see what it says.

414
00:33:59,625 --> 00:34:01,208
Your prediction
for luck looks fair

415
00:34:01,291 --> 00:34:03,041
but it's not very interesting.

416
00:34:03,125 --> 00:34:06,375
All the same - you seem
pretty happy about it.

417
00:34:06,458 --> 00:34:07,291
Ah-ha!

418
00:34:07,375 --> 00:34:08,458
This must be why!

419
00:34:08,541 --> 00:34:10,875
The one you await
will soon return!

420
00:34:10,958 --> 00:34:13,875
I wonder who that could be?

421
00:34:13,958 --> 00:34:15,125
I have no idea!

422
00:34:15,208 --> 00:34:17,208
Oh really?-I don't know...

423
00:34:17,291 --> 00:34:18,875
I was thinking
it might be Mr. Oo...

424
00:34:18,958 --> 00:34:20,416
Come on, now!

425
00:34:20,500 --> 00:34:22,000
We should be more concerned
about our new stage production.

426
00:34:22,083 --> 00:34:23,708
Right?

427
00:34:23,791 --> 00:34:24,875
I suppose.

428
00:34:24,958 --> 00:34:26,916
But I'm stuck with
a bit part in the play.

429
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:28,500
You've only got a bit part?

430
00:34:28,583 --> 00:34:33,416
Yeah And I've always liked the
author Kyouka's Izumi's work.

431
00:34:33,500 --> 00:34:35,250
Did Lachette really
get the starring role

432
00:34:35,333 --> 00:34:36,500
even though she just joined us?

433
00:34:36,583 --> 00:34:37,375
Yes-it's true.

434
00:34:37,458 --> 00:34:39,166
Won't it be exciting to see?!

435
00:34:39,250 --> 00:34:42,583
Okay everyone let's
do the next scene!

436
00:34:42,666 --> 00:34:43,916
Now remember...

437
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:45,541
This is the Dragon King's
Palace, and the prince

438
00:34:45,625 --> 00:34:47,750
has bought the girl he loves
with a gift of treasure

439
00:34:47,833 --> 00:34:49,916
for her father.
The exchange is agreed to,

440
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:51,708
and he's waiting
for the girl to come.

441
00:34:51,791 --> 00:34:53,208
Hear me, Souzu.

442
00:34:53,291 --> 00:34:54,000
Yes.

443
00:34:54,083 --> 00:34:55,500
What is it, young master.

444
00:34:55,583 --> 00:34:57,875
I wonder if they are
satisfied with the treasure

445
00:34:57,958 --> 00:35:00,375
that I sent to them in
exchange for their daughter.

446
00:35:00,458 --> 00:35:01,791
Do you think
it will please them?

447
00:35:01,875 --> 00:35:03,166
Yes, master.

448
00:35:03,250 --> 00:35:04,916
They would not have sent
their daughter if they were

449
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:08,291
not happy with the generous
gift you have given to them.

450
00:35:08,375 --> 00:35:11,583
Avarice truly runs
deep in all humans.

451
00:35:11,666 --> 00:35:14,000
But the dear maiden
that has won the affection

452
00:35:14,083 --> 00:35:16,916
of our young master
will enjoy true happiness.

453
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:20,125
I do so wish for
the fair maiden to arrive soon.

454
00:35:20,208 --> 00:35:21,083
Hmm?

455
00:35:21,166 --> 00:35:22,250
Alas!

456
00:35:22,333 --> 00:35:24,416
The bright beacon
of light has arrived!

457
00:35:24,500 --> 00:35:26,500
It appears that she is here!

458
00:35:27,708 --> 00:35:28,916
Are you alright Lachette?!

459
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:30,708
No problem-I'm fine!

460
00:35:31,708 --> 00:35:32,750
Aah!

461
00:35:32,833 --> 00:35:34,291
How can we fight like this!

462
00:35:34,375 --> 00:35:35,166
Everyone alright?!

463
00:35:35,250 --> 00:35:35,875
What do you think you're doing!

464
00:35:35,958 --> 00:35:37,041
C'mon, fix me up!

465
00:35:37,125 --> 00:35:39,958
Just a little more.

466
00:35:40,041 --> 00:35:41,583
Oh no-are we gonna have
to rely on the Yafqiels?

467
00:35:41,666 --> 00:35:43,083
Watch out!
They're focusing on Leni!

468
00:35:43,166 --> 00:35:44,833
Leni!

469
00:35:44,916 --> 00:35:46,291
No it's too late!

470
00:35:46,375 --> 00:35:47,750
Leni!

471
00:35:47,833 --> 00:35:50,666
To hell with this!

472
00:35:50,750 --> 00:35:52,041
Ms. Orihime!

473
00:35:53,625 --> 00:35:55,416
Two Koubu Kai units
of Flower Division

474
00:35:55,500 --> 00:35:58,083
suffered major damage
in the last engagement.

475
00:35:58,166 --> 00:36:00,916
And one of the members
was seriously injured.

476
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:03,416
The severely damaged Koubu Kai
units have been transported

477
00:36:03,500 --> 00:36:06,500
to the Kanzaki Heavy Industry
factory for repairs.

478
00:36:06,583 --> 00:36:08,958
For the duration of the
repairs, we plan on making do

479
00:36:09,041 --> 00:36:12,125
with two Eisenkleider's that
were previously mothballed.

480
00:36:14,166 --> 00:36:16,291
Next regarding the status
of the Imperial Army

481
00:36:16,375 --> 00:36:18,375
13th Special
Mechanized Squad...

482
00:36:18,458 --> 00:36:21,416
...5 Yafqiels were dispatched
and suffered no damage.

483
00:36:21,500 --> 00:36:23,833
Their Descending Demons
kill score appears to be

484
00:36:23,916 --> 00:36:27,333
significantly larger than
that of Flower Division.

485
00:36:27,416 --> 00:36:30,125
It would appear that
times have indeed changed.

486
00:36:30,208 --> 00:36:33,875
If I may be permitted to,
I would like to make a request.

487
00:36:33,958 --> 00:36:37,541
Actually This is
a very simple matter.

488
00:36:37,625 --> 00:36:39,708
A command of a Yafqiel unit?

489
00:36:39,791 --> 00:36:41,041
But this makes no sense!

490
00:36:41,125 --> 00:36:43,041
Why should we have
to do something like that?

491
00:36:43,125 --> 00:36:46,083
The military is a place where
you must always follow orders

492
00:36:46,166 --> 00:36:47,833
that come from your superiors.

493
00:36:47,916 --> 00:36:50,083
Of-course, ' But deploying
the Yafqiels' like this

494
00:36:50,166 --> 00:36:51,916
is extremely suspicious!

495
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:53,708
I've been informed
that their deployment

496
00:36:53,791 --> 00:36:56,416
is top secret and classified.

497
00:36:56,500 --> 00:36:58,375
Then what are we?
Window-dressing?

498
00:36:58,458 --> 00:37:01,041
Military officers will
be doing the commanding!

499
00:37:01,125 --> 00:37:02,916
This is hardly
window-dressing!

500
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:06,750
But this is like a de facto
break up of Flower Division!

501
00:37:06,833 --> 00:37:08,750
Even though we've been
relieved of intercepting

502
00:37:08,833 --> 00:37:11,125
the Descending Demons, it
doesn't mean Flower Division

503
00:37:11,208 --> 00:37:12,541
is going to be broken up.

504
00:37:13,875 --> 00:37:16,208
If this is their final word
I'll go to the Army.

505
00:37:16,291 --> 00:37:18,833
Oh really and just who
do you think you are?!

506
00:37:18,916 --> 00:37:21,666
In listening to
Lt. General Yoneda I feel that

507
00:37:21,750 --> 00:37:24,666
I would be the most appropriate
candidate for such a mission.

508
00:37:24,750 --> 00:37:25,750
Hmm...

509
00:37:25,833 --> 00:37:28,291
Well-I suppose
that Lachette would...

510
00:37:28,375 --> 00:37:29,458
I'm the one who should go!

511
00:37:29,541 --> 00:37:30,500
I want to go!

512
00:37:30,583 --> 00:37:32,083
I am GOING!!

513
00:37:32,166 --> 00:37:33,708
All right-all right, fine!

514
00:37:33,791 --> 00:37:35,958
If you want it that
much-then fine by me!

515
00:37:36,041 --> 00:37:38,000
You can go to
the Army-all right?!

516
00:37:40,166 --> 00:37:41,541
Hmph!

517
00:37:42,541 --> 00:37:44,291
Our next challenge,
is to figure out how

518
00:37:44,375 --> 00:37:46,958
to put together a production
in this state...

519
00:37:59,500 --> 00:38:00,500
Hm?

520
00:38:02,125 --> 00:38:02,958
What!

521
00:38:03,041 --> 00:38:04,250
Ugaah!

522
00:38:05,500 --> 00:38:07,375
Commander Yoneda is missing?!

523
00:38:07,458 --> 00:38:09,291
Commander Yoneda is missing?!

524
00:38:09,375 --> 00:38:11,583
Commander Yoneda is missing?!

525
00:38:11,666 --> 00:38:13,666
Both Moon Division
and Dream Division

526
00:38:13,750 --> 00:38:15,833
are currently doing
their best to locate him.

527
00:38:15,916 --> 00:38:19,083
Actually, Lt. General Yoneda
isn't the only one missing.

528
00:38:19,166 --> 00:38:22,541
Count Hanakouji
is missing as well.

529
00:38:22,625 --> 00:38:25,458
I'm afraid I have
another piece of bad news.

530
00:38:25,541 --> 00:38:27,541
The operation of the
Imperial Operetta Troupe

531
00:38:27,625 --> 00:38:29,541
has been indefinitely
suspended.

532
00:38:29,625 --> 00:38:30,875
Suspended?!

533
00:38:30,958 --> 00:38:32,750
We are to relocate to the
Flower Mansion Branch

534
00:38:32,833 --> 00:38:33,958
right away.

535
00:38:34,041 --> 00:38:35,500
The Imperial Theater
complex will be under

536
00:38:35,583 --> 00:38:37,208
the command of the Army.

537
00:38:37,291 --> 00:38:38,041
That can't be...

538
00:38:38,125 --> 00:38:39,708
Oh no...

539
00:38:42,666 --> 00:38:44,250
The Yafqiels squad
has requested dispatch

540
00:38:44,333 --> 00:38:46,083
of their commanding officer.

541
00:38:47,333 --> 00:38:49,375
I'll go right now.

542
00:38:49,458 --> 00:38:51,083
Orihime...

543
00:38:51,166 --> 00:38:52,708
Make us proud as
a former member

544
00:38:52,791 --> 00:38:55,833
of the Star Division, Orihime.

545
00:38:55,916 --> 00:38:58,166
This has nothing to do
with Star Division.

546
00:38:58,250 --> 00:39:01,583
Right now, I am
a member of Flower Division.

547
00:39:06,375 --> 00:39:08,916
Everyone prepare
to pack your belongings.

548
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:11,916
We will head out to the
Flower Mansion in one hour.

549
00:39:13,833 --> 00:39:16,458
Ms. Orihime...

550
00:39:16,541 --> 00:39:19,875
Ms. Orihime, disembark from
the Gourai-Go at Nihonbashi,

551
00:39:19,958 --> 00:39:22,541
and head to Fukagawa
from there on land.

552
00:39:22,625 --> 00:39:24,291
Roger that.

553
00:39:24,375 --> 00:39:25,875
Orihime...

554
00:39:25,958 --> 00:39:28,083
As a proud member
of the Flower Division

555
00:39:28,166 --> 00:39:30,000
I am ready for the challenge.

556
00:39:30,083 --> 00:39:31,750
'N' that's why...

557
00:39:31,833 --> 00:39:35,458
I refuse to allow Lachette
to try and out do me again!

558
00:39:56,583 --> 00:39:58,333
It's amazing how well
these things are able

559
00:39:58,416 --> 00:40:00,291
to move on their own.

560
00:40:10,500 --> 00:40:12,291
Where are the
Descending Demons?!

561
00:40:41,750 --> 00:40:43,166
There you go!

562
00:40:46,416 --> 00:40:48,958
There you go birdies!

563
00:40:49,041 --> 00:40:50,625
Catch-it! 

564
00:40:56,958 --> 00:40:59,375
There you go! You got it!

565
00:41:00,875 --> 00:41:02,250
Here!

566
00:41:04,208 --> 00:41:05,666
I wonder how Orihime is?

567
00:41:05,750 --> 00:41:07,500
I hope she's managing well.

568
00:41:07,583 --> 00:41:08,708
Yes I know.

569
00:41:08,791 --> 00:41:11,041
I'm sorry to say but
information no longer

570
00:41:11,125 --> 00:41:13,125
comes my way.

571
00:41:13,208 --> 00:41:14,750
Oh. I see...

572
00:41:15,958 --> 00:41:19,833
I wonder if we'll ever be able
to ride the Koubu's again.

573
00:41:19,916 --> 00:41:22,875
If it means that the
peace of Tokyo is secure

574
00:41:22,958 --> 00:41:26,000
then there's nothing
wrong with that.

575
00:41:26,083 --> 00:41:27,375
But what if...

576
00:41:27,458 --> 00:41:30,208
What if the Flower Divsion
were to be disbanded...

577
00:41:51,291 --> 00:41:53,083
All the Yafqiels on
this production line

578
00:41:53,166 --> 00:41:54,666
are empty shells...

579
00:41:54,750 --> 00:41:56,458
Where'er the insides?

580
00:42:10,916 --> 00:42:12,041
Ah!!

581
00:42:18,166 --> 00:42:20,541
This is what's
inside the Yafqiels?

582
00:42:22,833 --> 00:42:24,375
The demons?

583
00:42:24,458 --> 00:42:26,583
Oh no what have they done?!

584
00:42:35,041 --> 00:42:37,791
It's a pleasure
to meet you, Maria.

585
00:42:37,875 --> 00:42:39,000
How flattering.

586
00:42:39,083 --> 00:42:40,583
Are you one of my fans?

587
00:42:40,666 --> 00:42:42,708
My name is Patrick.

588
00:42:42,791 --> 00:42:45,375
As you are about to die,
I thought I should

589
00:42:45,458 --> 00:42:48,125
reveal my real name to you.

590
00:42:49,333 --> 00:42:51,500
You have learned too much!!

591
00:42:56,958 --> 00:43:01,833
Unfortunately for you,
bullets have no effect on me.

592
00:43:17,500 --> 00:43:19,250
Maria did what?!

593
00:43:19,333 --> 00:43:21,125
I heard she left behind
a note saying she was

594
00:43:21,208 --> 00:43:23,208
going to investigate
Douglas-Stewart.

595
00:43:23,291 --> 00:43:25,000
They say, no one's
heard from her since.

596
00:43:25,083 --> 00:43:26,541
Let's go look for her!

597
00:43:26,625 --> 00:43:28,583
Yes! We should act recklessly.

598
00:43:28,666 --> 00:43:29,416
Huh?!

599
00:43:29,500 --> 00:43:31,708
But, I don't know...

600
00:43:31,791 --> 00:43:33,916
There's no need
to worry about Ms. Maria.

601
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:36,583
She knows what she's doing -
After all she's our captain.

602
00:43:36,666 --> 00:43:38,500
I know but does that mean
we're supposed to just

603
00:43:38,583 --> 00:43:40,833
sit here and do
nothing at all?!

604
00:43:42,250 --> 00:43:44,541
I never did
give this to her...

605
00:43:44,625 --> 00:43:47,708
I made this special bullet
filled with spirit power...

606
00:43:49,125 --> 00:43:52,208
I only managed to get
one round to Mr. Kayama...

607
00:43:52,291 --> 00:43:54,333
Gotta do what you can
while you can or,

608
00:43:54,416 --> 00:43:56,541
you might end up regretting it.

609
00:43:59,541 --> 00:44:01,708
What can we do I ask you?!

610
00:44:01,791 --> 00:44:03,458
Shougei-Maru has been sealed...

611
00:44:03,541 --> 00:44:05,583
Wind Division and the Deputy
Commander are being held

612
00:44:05,666 --> 00:44:07,833
at the Imperial Theater House.

613
00:44:07,916 --> 00:44:10,083
What can we do
in such a predicament?!

614
00:44:15,541 --> 00:44:16,916
Hey. I know - Why not?

615
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:18,125
Hm?

616
00:44:18,208 --> 00:44:19,958
Do what we can while we can!

617
00:44:21,375 --> 00:44:24,875
I don't want to live
with regrets in my heart.

618
00:44:24,958 --> 00:44:27,041
Come on.
Let's do this together!

619
00:44:27,125 --> 00:44:28,000
Let's do it!

620
00:44:28,083 --> 00:44:28,875
Let's do it!

621
00:44:28,958 --> 00:44:30,000
Let's go for it!

622
00:44:30,083 --> 00:44:30,833
I'm with you!

623
00:44:30,916 --> 00:44:32,333
I suppose that we must.

624
00:44:32,416 --> 00:44:33,791
I agree!

625
00:44:33,875 --> 00:44:35,875
Mr. Yokihiko from
the Rose Division!

626
00:44:35,958 --> 00:44:38,833
This entire affair seems to
involve a segment of the Army

627
00:44:38,916 --> 00:44:40,333
that has been
incited into action

628
00:44:40,416 --> 00:44:42,833
by a particular
politician named Tanuma.

629
00:44:42,916 --> 00:44:44,708
It appears that
Douglas-Stewart and Tanuma

630
00:44:44,791 --> 00:44:46,708
have been scheming together.

631
00:44:46,791 --> 00:44:49,125
Moon Division is searching
for Commander Yoneda

632
00:44:49,208 --> 00:44:51,250
and Count Hanakouji.

633
00:44:51,333 --> 00:44:54,708
Let's go to
the Great Imperial Theater!

634
00:44:54,791 --> 00:44:57,125
We'll use the underground
waterways to go from Hibiya

635
00:44:57,208 --> 00:45:01,041
to the HQ hangers, and get
your Koubu Kai's there.

636
00:45:01,125 --> 00:45:03,541
We have underground waterways?

637
00:45:03,625 --> 00:45:05,083
Yes!

638
00:45:05,166 --> 00:45:06,958
We had them made when we were
building the subway system.

639
00:45:07,041 --> 00:45:09,708
But how are we supposed to get
around all of those waterways?

640
00:45:09,791 --> 00:45:12,125
Ha ha ha.

641
00:45:12,208 --> 00:45:13,791
No problem at all.

642
00:45:13,875 --> 00:45:15,708
I designed and created
a secret machine

643
00:45:15,791 --> 00:45:17,250
for urgent cases like this...

644
00:45:17,333 --> 00:45:19,500
...It's called Katsuryu-Maru!

645
00:45:24,583 --> 00:45:27,750
Hey Kouran what's with all those
machines you've got on board?

646
00:45:27,833 --> 00:45:30,375
Oh those are just the upgrade
components that I designed

647
00:45:30,458 --> 00:45:32,750
for the Eisenkleider
and the Koubu Kai's!

648
00:45:32,833 --> 00:45:34,791
Just wait
'til you see the rest!

649
00:45:42,666 --> 00:45:46,375
Quite a picturesque
cityscape at dusk, isn't it?

650
00:45:49,875 --> 00:45:51,916
But of course it
pales in comparison

651
00:45:52,000 --> 00:45:54,750
to the city of New York.

652
00:45:54,833 --> 00:45:58,083
And what exactly is it
you brought us here to see?

653
00:46:18,291 --> 00:46:21,666
You continue to market
these things-now?

654
00:46:21,750 --> 00:46:23,125
Hmph.

655
00:46:46,833 --> 00:46:49,125
Good-God may
heaven help us...

656
00:46:50,625 --> 00:46:53,166
An impressive sight
isn't it Count?

657
00:47:05,625 --> 00:47:07,916
So this is where it leads to.

658
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:10,041
We'll have better mobility
if we all split up.

659
00:47:10,125 --> 00:47:11,250
Yeah you're right!

660
00:47:13,333 --> 00:47:14,333
All clear!

661
00:47:18,041 --> 00:47:19,666
Hey! Halt there!

662
00:47:20,875 --> 00:47:21,958
Sakura!

663
00:47:26,833 --> 00:47:28,041
Damn

664
00:47:36,458 --> 00:47:37,375
No!

665
00:47:37,458 --> 00:47:38,833
No!!!

666
00:47:42,208 --> 00:47:43,791
Don't you think
you're going too far...

667
00:47:43,875 --> 00:47:45,041
Ms. Lachette.

668
00:47:45,125 --> 00:47:45,916
Really?

669
00:47:46,000 --> 00:47:47,500
Didn't I make myself clear?

670
00:47:47,583 --> 00:47:51,250
I simply prefer adopting
the most efficient option.

671
00:47:51,333 --> 00:47:54,541
Nevertheless I think it's time
to return to our Koubu's.

672
00:47:56,791 --> 00:47:58,208
Identify yourself!

673
00:47:58,291 --> 00:47:59,375
Flower Division.

674
00:47:59,458 --> 00:48:01,583
We've come here
to take back our theater.

675
00:48:02,458 --> 00:48:03,541
Kanna...

676
00:48:04,416 --> 00:48:05,208
Stand down!

677
00:48:05,291 --> 00:48:06,625
You're out of line young lady.

678
00:48:06,708 --> 00:48:08,708
You've been ordered to standby
at the Flower Mansion!

679
00:48:08,791 --> 00:48:09,541
Hmph!

680
00:48:09,625 --> 00:48:10,916
I don't think I can do that.

681
00:48:11,000 --> 00:48:13,041
If I stayed there any longer
I'd go nuts from Sumire

682
00:48:13,125 --> 00:48:14,125
and her hysterics.

683
00:48:14,208 --> 00:48:14,875
Huh? Ms. Kanna?!

684
00:48:14,958 --> 00:48:16,000
Enough of this nonsense!

685
00:48:16,083 --> 00:48:17,416
Don't you respect orders?!

686
00:48:17,500 --> 00:48:18,625
Of course!

687
00:48:18,708 --> 00:48:20,333
We'll obey any order
as long as it's designed

688
00:48:20,416 --> 00:48:22,000
to safeguard Tokyo.

689
00:48:22,083 --> 00:48:25,416
You tell me how cozying up to
Douglas-Stewart is gonna help.

690
00:48:25,500 --> 00:48:28,166
You think that's gonna
make this city any safer?!

691
00:48:31,333 --> 00:48:33,375
Deputy Commander...

692
00:48:33,458 --> 00:48:35,750
Ever since
Commander Yoneda has been gone

693
00:48:35,833 --> 00:48:39,458
I guess I lost my nerve
without realizing.

694
00:48:39,541 --> 00:48:40,625
Shame on me.

695
00:48:40,708 --> 00:48:42,083
In times like this
I suppose I should be

696
00:48:42,166 --> 00:48:43,833
the one standing strong.

697
00:48:43,916 --> 00:48:46,666
You all taught me a very
valuable lesson today.

698
00:48:46,750 --> 00:48:48,875
Let's do it, Deputy Commander!

699
00:48:48,958 --> 00:48:51,041
I'll start upgrading
the Koubu Kai's.

700
00:48:51,125 --> 00:48:53,291
There's a whole lot
we gotta do here guys

701
00:48:53,375 --> 00:48:56,000
so any extra help
would be great!

702
00:48:56,083 --> 00:48:59,791
Fighting Troupe Flower Division
prepare for dispatch!

703
00:49:03,750 --> 00:49:05,500
What is it that
you hope to accomplish?

704
00:49:05,583 --> 00:49:07,916
It appears that the fair
maidens of the Flower Division

705
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:10,791
intend to defy us
no matter what happens.

706
00:49:10,875 --> 00:49:15,500
I believe some discipline
is in order here...

707
00:49:15,583 --> 00:49:17,458
Wouldn't you agree?

708
00:49:19,750 --> 00:49:21,875
Or what if we were to
propose being entrusted

709
00:49:21,958 --> 00:49:24,041
to safeguard Tokyo?

710
00:49:24,125 --> 00:49:27,000
Would you be willing
to accept such a proposition?

711
00:49:27,083 --> 00:49:28,875
We're not in need
of your assistance.

712
00:49:28,958 --> 00:49:32,000
We shall guard
our imperial capital alone!

713
00:49:34,333 --> 00:49:35,708
Listen to me.

714
00:49:35,791 --> 00:49:37,791
Do you have any idea what
it is that those brave girls

715
00:49:37,875 --> 00:49:39,083
are fighting for?

716
00:49:39,166 --> 00:49:41,291
Can you even begin
to fathom what goes through

717
00:49:41,375 --> 00:49:43,208
their minds and what
they are made of?

718
00:49:43,291 --> 00:49:46,041
Can you not understand
what they wish for?

719
00:49:48,500 --> 00:49:49,916
Those girls are damn tough.

720
00:49:50,000 --> 00:49:51,916
They've done a fine job
keeping this city safe

721
00:49:52,000 --> 00:49:53,833
and they will
continue to do so.

722
00:49:53,916 --> 00:49:56,166
And further more
I believe in them.

723
00:49:58,500 --> 00:50:00,083
Descending Demons in Ginza!

724
00:50:00,166 --> 00:50:01,458
Huge numbers, Ma'am.

725
00:50:39,541 --> 00:50:40,791
Listen up everyone!

726
00:50:40,875 --> 00:50:42,375
With the backpacks you're
wearing that I invented

727
00:50:42,458 --> 00:50:45,000
your maneuverability
has increased 120%!

728
00:50:45,083 --> 00:50:46,416
Time to get cracking!!

729
00:50:58,958 --> 00:51:00,083
Behold!

730
00:51:00,166 --> 00:51:03,208
We - are - the Imperial
Fighting - Troupe!!

731
00:51:04,541 --> 00:51:07,125
It's our-duty '
to protect this great city!!

732
00:51:54,750 --> 00:51:55,666
Ms. Kaede!

733
00:51:55,750 --> 00:51:57,875
It looks like
we're ready to go!

734
00:51:57,958 --> 00:52:00,500
Our spirit power
is building up just fine!

735
00:52:00,583 --> 00:52:01,458
Understood!

736
00:52:01,541 --> 00:52:04,083
Get into formation
and standby!

737
00:52:04,166 --> 00:52:06,750
The Dream Division is
ready and waiting Ma'am.

738
00:52:22,916 --> 00:52:24,250
Adequate spirit
power build-up!

739
00:52:24,333 --> 00:52:26,041
Critical level reached!

740
00:52:26,125 --> 00:52:28,750
Imperial Capital
Barricade Formation!!

741
00:52:52,291 --> 00:52:52,958
Hey!

742
00:52:53,041 --> 00:52:54,041
Look!

743
00:52:54,958 --> 00:52:56,250
Yafqiel!

744
00:52:58,083 --> 00:52:59,916
What the hell do you
think you're doing?!

745
00:53:09,250 --> 00:53:10,125
Leni!

746
00:53:13,625 --> 00:53:15,041
Leni!!

747
00:53:36,791 --> 00:53:37,958
Is that her?!

748
00:53:42,625 --> 00:53:44,333
Ms. Orihime...

749
00:53:54,625 --> 00:53:55,708
Orihime!

750
00:53:55,791 --> 00:53:57,375
Ms. Orihime!

751
00:54:20,958 --> 00:54:22,250
Ms. Orihime!

752
00:54:29,166 --> 00:54:30,416
Aah!

753
00:54:32,791 --> 00:54:33,750
Look - out!

754
00:54:36,291 --> 00:54:37,416
Orihime!

755
00:54:47,500 --> 00:54:48,666
Orihime!

756
00:54:48,750 --> 00:54:49,625
Wake up please!

757
00:54:49,708 --> 00:54:50,791
Come on!

758
00:54:51,958 --> 00:54:53,583
I'm-sorry-but, '
We must bring an end

759
00:54:53,666 --> 00:54:55,958
to this meaningless
waste of time Orihime.

760
00:54:58,791 --> 00:54:59,833
Ms. Lachette, please wait!

761
00:54:59,916 --> 00:55:01,416
There must be another way!!

762
00:55:04,708 --> 00:55:06,625
You must stay out of my way!

763
00:55:06,708 --> 00:55:07,875
What are you doing?!

764
00:55:15,750 --> 00:55:16,916
Ugh!

765
00:55:22,000 --> 00:55:22,791
No!!

766
00:55:51,583 --> 00:55:52,416
Leni!

767
00:56:04,500 --> 00:56:05,291
Leni!

768
00:56:05,375 --> 00:56:06,416
Hold on!

769
00:56:09,291 --> 00:56:11,291
Oh. Thanks so much.

770
00:56:11,375 --> 00:56:12,083
Leni!

771
00:56:12,166 --> 00:56:13,750
Are you OK?!

772
00:56:13,833 --> 00:56:16,250
I'm fine, Iris.

773
00:56:16,333 --> 00:56:17,666
Thank God.

774
00:56:44,083 --> 00:56:45,666
Orihime!!

775
00:56:48,083 --> 00:56:48,916
Ms. Orihime!

776
00:56:49,000 --> 00:56:49,583
Orihime!

777
00:56:49,666 --> 00:56:50,666
Orihime!

778
00:56:59,166 --> 00:56:59,916
Orihime!

779
00:57:00,916 --> 00:57:02,000
Orihime!

780
00:57:12,916 --> 00:57:14,291
I'm so sorry.

781
00:57:14,375 --> 00:57:16,583
I guess I really
blew it this time.

782
00:57:38,250 --> 00:57:41,541
Hmph.

783
00:57:41,625 --> 00:57:45,000
I'm sorry we were delayed,
Count, Lt. General.

784
00:57:45,083 --> 00:57:46,416
You needn't worry any more.

785
00:57:46,500 --> 00:57:49,125
We've completely secured
